text.section:
In this section, "human service facility" means a facility licensed by the State that is:
a nursing home, as defined in § 19-1401 of the Health - General Article;
an assisted living facility, as defined in § 19-1801 of the Health - General Article;
a hospital, as defined in § 19-301 of the Health - General Article;
a related institution as defined in § 19-301 of the Health - General Article;
a State-operated institution for mental disease;
a group home as defined in § 7-101 of the Health - General Article;
an alternative living unit as defined in § 7-101 of the Health - General Article; and
a State residential center as defined in § 7-101 of the Health - General Article.

section.section:
Regulations adopted under paragraph (1) of this subsection shall be developed in consultation with representatives of:
the Maryland Emergency Management Agency;
the Maryland Institute for Emergency Medical Services Systems;
local organizations for emergency management; and
human service facilities.
